On behalf of the consortium of
Latin American Studies programs,

00:05:18.630 --> 00:05:22.740
Vanderbilt University and Tulane
University, we welcome you

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:25.820
to the 25th ceremony
of these awards.

00:05:25.820 --> 00:05:31.120
We are very excited to be here,
sharing the ceremony with you

00:05:31.120 --> 00:05:34.990
across the country, streaming
with fans across the country,

00:05:34.990 --> 00:05:36.830
with our class members.

00:05:36.830 --> 00:05:41.070
It's a great addition this year
to be streaming and celebrating

00:05:41.070 --> 00:05:44.650
and engaging with the award with
communities across the country.

00:05:44.650 --> 00:05:47.850
Our co-sponsors of this year's
award are working with teachers

00:05:47.850 --> 00:05:50.770
to develop curriculum that
correspond with books,

00:05:50.770 --> 00:05:56.010
forming book clubs, creating
book trailers, and much more.

00:05:56.010 --> 00:05:58.140
The awards are administered
by the consortium

00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:00.440
of Latin American Studies
programs and coordinated

00:06:00.440 --> 00:06:02.650
by both Tulane and Vanderbilt.

00:06:02.650 --> 00:06:06.320
Generous support
is also provided

00:06:06.320 --> 00:06:09.710
by Florida International
University, Stanford University,

00:06:09.710 --> 00:06:13.040
the Ohio State University,
UNC Duke consortium

00:06:13.040 --> 00:06:15.770
in Latin American and Caribbean
studies, the University

00:06:15.770 --> 00:06:18.590
of Florida, the University
of New Mexico, the University

00:06:18.590 --> 00:06:22.260
of Texas at Austin, University
of Utah, and the University

00:06:22.260 --> 00:06:23.830
of Wisconsin Milwaukee.

00:06:23.830 --> 00:06:26.400
A lot of really great
support from our centers

00:06:26.400 --> 00:06:28.330
from across the country.

00:06:28.330 --> 00:06:31.400
Our awards are given up to two
books each year and are selected

00:06:31.400 --> 00:06:33.510
for their distinctive
literary quality,

00:06:33.510 --> 00:06:37.320
cultural contextualization,
exceptional integration of text,

00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:41.510
illustration and design and
potential for classroom use.

00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:44.180
The goal of this award
is to link the Americas,

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:48.010
to reach beyond geographic
borders, focusing instead

00:06:48.010 --> 00:06:50.430
on cultural heritages
within the hemisphere.

00:06:50.430 --> 00:06:55.630
I'd like to take a moment to
say thank you to our committee.

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:58.080
Many of our committee members
are here with us today.

00:06:58.080 --> 00:07:01.640
This year's Americas Award
review committee was comprised

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:05.770
of teachers, librarians,
faculty, and community activists

00:07:05.770 --> 00:07:11.350
from Tennessee, Texas, Illinois,
North Carolina and Wisconsin.

00:07:11.350 --> 00:07:14.760
This year Paula Mason was
our chair of the committee.

00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:17.340
She is a librarian for the
Waukesha Public Library

00:07:17.340 --> 00:07:18.640
in Wisconsin.

00:07:18.640 --> 00:07:21.660
Just to give you an
idea of the process

00:07:21.660 --> 00:07:22.960
that our committee goes through.

00:07:22.960 --> 00:07:26.030
In the fall, books arrive,
throughout the year.

00:07:26.030 --> 00:07:28.670
By January we have our list.

00:07:28.670 --> 00:07:34.430
We set up Skype calls in the
spring and chat for hours

00:07:34.430 --> 00:07:37.150
over weekends about
amazing books,

00:07:37.150 --> 00:07:40.360
and they are spirited
conversations

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:43.640
about the diverse cultures of
Latin America and the Caribbean.

00:07:43.640 --> 00:07:45.970
Coleen and I are extremely
grateful for the hard work

00:07:45.970 --> 00:07:47.640
of the committee, and
the care that they put

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:51.090
into this year's award
winners, the honorable mentions,

00:07:51.090 --> 00:07:54.170
and the commended titles.

00:07:54.170 --> 00:07:59.310
I'd like to share some
messages about our founder

00:07:59.310 --> 00:08:00.840
of the Americas Award, Julie.

00:08:00.840 --> 00:08:04.390
The Americas Award began
as an idea 25 years ago

00:08:04.390 --> 00:08:06.220
by my colleague, Julie.

00:08:06.220 --> 00:08:08.900
She is the associate director
at the Center for Latin American

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:10.630
and Caribbean studies
at the University

00:08:10.630 --> 00:08:13.800
of Wisconsin Milwaukee,
a member of class.

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:17.280
She started the award when no
other award recognizing Latin

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:20.040
America and Latino
culture in children's

00:08:20.040 --> 00:08:23.130
and young adult literature
yet existed.

00:08:23.130 --> 00:08:26.470
Her idea became one of the most
important projects of class.

00:08:26.470 --> 00:08:29.620
It has enabled scholars of
Latin America to come together

00:08:29.620 --> 00:08:33.800
and engage with children's
literature in many diverse ways.

00:08:33.800 --> 00:08:37.220
It has become our passion and
our responsibility to educators

00:08:37.220 --> 00:08:40.110
to read and share authentic
and engaging literature

00:08:40.110 --> 00:08:41.650
for the K12 classroom.

00:08:41.650 --> 00:08:44.300
I want to thank Julie
by presenting

00:08:44.300 --> 00:08:47.660
to her a symbol she
once created years ago,

00:08:47.660 --> 00:08:50.850
a weaving from Guatemala
that represents the weaving

00:08:50.850 --> 00:08:53.230
of stories and voices
of the Americas.

00:08:53.230 --> 00:08:55.210
I'd like to invite my
daughter, Valeca [phonetic],

00:08:55.210 --> 00:08:58.970
to share our token of thanks.

