00:45:13.210 --> 00:45:16.540
Thank you to the Consortium of
Latin American Studies programs

00:45:16.540 --> 00:45:18.000
and all of these
years' sponsors.

00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:21.950
And thank you to an
incredible review committee,

00:45:21.950 --> 00:45:24.670
especially the committee
chair, Paula Mason.

00:45:24.670 --> 00:45:27.190
The thoughtfulness and the
dedication of the award

00:45:27.190 --> 00:45:30.790
of each committee member
is truly inspiring.

00:45:30.790 --> 00:45:35.160
The Americas Award is not
just a children's book award

00:45:35.160 --> 00:45:38.160
but also represents a
variety of resources

00:45:38.160 --> 00:45:40.400
for teachers and librarians.

00:45:40.400 --> 00:45:43.610
To commemorate this
special 25th anniversary,

00:45:43.610 --> 00:45:46.190
we have put together a
comprehensive toolkit

00:45:46.190 --> 00:45:50.240
for teachers, librarians, and
outreach professionals to use

00:45:50.240 --> 00:45:54.540
as a guide for engaging with
books recognized by the award.

00:45:54.540 --> 00:45:58.690
This toolkit provides classroom
activities, curriculum,

00:45:58.690 --> 00:46:01.910
ideas for community events
and teacher workshops,

00:46:01.910 --> 00:46:04.680
and many other resources
and will soon be available

00:46:04.680 --> 00:46:08.360
on the class website
shown in your program.

00:46:08.360 --> 00:46:10.970
We extend our gratitude
to Keira Philipp-Schnurer

00:46:10.970 --> 00:46:12.980
from the University
of New Mexico

00:46:12.980 --> 00:46:15.970
for leading this special
project and for her work

00:46:15.970 --> 00:46:19.820
